 {"id":"bd-uqdk","title":"Implement read_line_limited helper function","description":"## Task Description

Implement a helper function that reads a line from input with a maximum length limit, failing fast before allocating excessive memory.

## Implementation

### Location

Add to src/interactive.rs (private helper, not exported):

```rust
/// Read a line from input with a maximum byte length limit.
/// 
/// Unlike `BufRead::read_line`, this function enforces the limit during reading
/// rather than after, preventing memory exhaustion from extremely long input.
/// 
/// # Arguments
/// * `reader` - Buffered reader to read from
/// * `max_bytes` - Maximum allowed input length in bytes (including newline)
/// 
/// # Returns
/// * `Ok(String)` - The line read (including trailing newline if present)
/// * `Err(PromptError::InputTooLong)` - Input exceeded limit
/// * `Err(PromptError::Eof)` - Reader reached EOF with no input
/// * `Err(PromptError::IoError)` - Underlying I/O error
/// 
/// # Example
/// ```ignore
/// let mut reader = io::Cursor::new("short input\n");
/// let line = read_line_limited(&mut reader, 1024)?;
/// assert_eq\!(line, "short input\n");
/// ```
fn read_line_limited<R: BufRead>(reader: &mut R, max_bytes: usize) -> Result<String, PromptError> {
    let mut result = Vec::with_capacity(max_bytes.min(1024));
    let mut total_read = 0usize;

    loop {
        let available = reader.fill_buf().map_err(PromptError::IoError)?;

        if available.is_empty() {
            // EOF reached
            if result.is_empty() {
                return Err(PromptError::Eof);
            }
            break;
        }

        // Look for newline in available buffer
        if let Some(newline_pos) = available.iter().position(|&b| b == b'\n') {
            let bytes_needed = newline_pos + 1; // Include the newline

            if total_read + bytes_needed > max_bytes {
                return Err(PromptError::InputTooLong {
                    limit: max_bytes,
                    received: total_read + bytes_needed,
                });
            }

            result.extend_from_slice(&available[..bytes_needed]);
            reader.consume(bytes_needed);
            break;
        }

        // No newline found, check if we would exceed limit
        if total_read + available.len() > max_bytes {
            return Err(PromptError::InputTooLong {
                limit: max_bytes,
                received: total_read + available.len(),
            });
        }

        // Append all available bytes and continue
        result.extend_from_slice(available);
        total_read += available.len();
        let len = available.len();
        reader.consume(len);
    }

    // Convert to String, handling potential UTF-8 errors
    String::from_utf8(result)
        .map_err(|e| PromptError::InvalidInput(format\!("invalid UTF-8: {e}")))
}
